Interface BagInterface<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
LinkedBag, ResizableArrayBag
public interface BagInterface<T>
An interface that displays the operations of a bag containing items

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    boolean add​(T newEntry)
    Adds a new entry to this bag
    void clear()
    Removes all entries from this bag
    boolean contains​(T anEntry)
    Tests whether this bag contains a given entry.
    BagInterface<T> difference​(BagInterface<T> anotherBag)
    Creates a bag of items that would occur if the similar items from both bags were taken out
    int getCurrentSize()
    Gets the current number of entries in the bag
    int getFrequencyOf​(T anEntry)
    Counts the number of times a given entry appears in this bag
    BagInterface<T> intersection​(BagInterface<T> anotherBag)
    Creates a new bag that contains the items that occur in both anotherBag and the primary bag
    boolean isEmpty()
    Checks whether the bag is empty
    T remove()
    Removes one unspecified entry from this bag if possible
    boolean remove​(T anEntry)
    Removes one occurrence of a given entry from this bag if possible
    T[] toArray()
    Retrieves all entries that are in this bag
    BagInterface<T> union​(BagInterface<T> anotherBag)
    Creates a new bag that has both the contents of the first bag and the second bag

  • Method Details

    • getCurrentSize

      int getCurrentSize()
      Gets the current number of entries in the bag
      Returns:
      The integer number of entries currently in the bag

    • isEmpty

      boolean isEmpty()
      Checks whether the bag is empty
      Returns:
      True if the bag is empty or False if the bag is not

    • add

      boolean add​(T newEntry)
      Adds a new entry to this bag
      Parameters:
      newEntry - The object which will be added as a new entry
      Returns:
      True if the addition is successful, or false if it is not

    • remove

      T remove()
      Removes one unspecified entry from this bag if possible
      Returns:
      Either the removed entry if the removal was successful or null if it was not successful

    • remove

      boolean remove​(T anEntry)
      Removes one occurrence of a given entry from this bag if possible
      Parameters:
      anEntry - The entry to be removed
      Returns:
      True if the removal was successful or false if it is not successful

    • clear

      void clear()
      Removes all entries from this bag

    • getFrequencyOf

      int getFrequencyOf​(T anEntry)
      Counts the number of times a given entry appears in this bag
      Parameters:
      anEntry - The entry to be counted
      Returns:
      The number of times anEntry appears in the bag

    • contains

      boolean contains​(T anEntry)
      Tests whether this bag contains a given entry.
      Parameters:
      anEntry - The entry to find
      Returns:
      True if the bag contains anEntry or false if it does not

    • toArray

      T[] toArray()
      Retrieves all entries that are in this bag
      Returns:
      A newly allocated array of all the entries in the bag. Note: If the bag is empty, the returned array is empty

    • union

      BagInterface<T> union​(BagInterface<T> anotherBag)
      Creates a new bag that has both the contents of the first bag and the second bag
      Parameters:
      anotherBag - The bag that is to be added to the primary bag
      Returns:
      The bag that has both the contents of anotherBag and the primary bag

    • intersection

      BagInterface<T> intersection​(BagInterface<T> anotherBag)
      Creates a new bag that contains the items that occur in both anotherBag and the primary bag
      Parameters:
      anotherBag - The bag that is to be compared to the primary bag
      Returns:
      A new bag with the entries that appear in BOTH the specified bag and the passed arguement

    • difference

      BagInterface<T> difference​(BagInterface<T> anotherBag)
      Creates a bag of items that would occur if the similar items from both bags were taken out
      Parameters:
      anotherBag - The bag that is to be removed
      Returns:
      A new bag with the non overlapping entries
